column5: Found a set of keys this morning on the Oakville Pier. Looks like a house key an a couple of others.  If they are yours send me a PM and I will get them back to you.  Burt
Those are uhhh mine, do they have an address on them?
I already took the Porsche fob off it and am feverishly scoping all the rich neighbourhoods in Oakville  Burt
Here's a hint for you Burt. Porsche owners usually live in a large house with garden furniture in the dining room and half a bottle of ketchup in the fridge.
The real shame isn't what's in the guy's fridge, but that they make cars like that in an automatic transmission.
I think we have another question to answer here, what is the owner of a porche doing at a pier?
my friends dad sometimes drives us to the pier in his 911 carrera 4S
Cant be worse than the jump seats in the back of my Ranger

One thing many learn way too late in life, or never for that matter. Never judge a person by the clothes they wear, the vehicle they drive or the house they live in. Chances are none of those tell anything of relevance!
What about the plane they fly?
LOL..  yah that too! I built mine with me own two hands...
